title: Razor Clam Chowder with Black Truffles, Turnips and Thyme
summary: The recipe Razor Clam Chowder with Black Truffles, Turnips and Thyme is ready in around 45 minutes and is definitely a great gluten free and pescatarian option for lovers of American food. For $1.3 per serving, you get a soup that serves 17. One serving contains 104 calories, 2g of protein, and 8g of fat. Head to the store and pick up turnip, heavy cream, butter, and a few other things to make it today. 14 people have made this recipe and would make it again. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 14%. This score is not so spectacular. Try Zucchini and Razor Clam Fritters, Clam Chowder, and Clam Chowder for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Clams can be paired with Chardonnay, Muscadet, and Riesling. Buttery chardonnay is great for scallops, shrimp, crab, and lobster, while muscadet is a classic pick for mussels, oysters, and clams. If you've got some spice in your shellfish, a semi-dry riesling can balance out the heat. The Gundlach Bundschu Chardonnay with a 4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 20 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Gundlach Bundschu Chardonnay
productMatches.description: With a refreshing purity of what this varietal can achieve on Rhinefarm’s 158-year old slice of Sonoma, the 2015 GundlachBundschu Chardonnay is a perfect example of fruit, texture, and balance. Leading with our old vine-driven aromatics of white blossoms, fresh lemon curd, and a hint of oak, the lush,mouth-filling palate is framed by bright acidity and citrus zest with flavors of white peach, spiced green apple, and a harmoniously creamy yet minerally finish.Style of Chardonnay:This wine represents the balanced style of Chardonnay in our Wine Discovery Set.Find more balanced Chardonnay.
